{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"group-search","type":"group","x":-1520,"y":-1680,"width":2280,"height":1320,"label":"Search Mega Group"},
		{"id":"group-raven","type":"group","x":-1920,"y":-100,"width":3600,"height":740,"label":"Raven Mega Group"},
		{"id":"group-ranking-draft-session","type":"group","x":560,"y":1200,"width":1720,"height":1380,"label":"Ranking Mega Group"},
		{"id":"group-future","type":"group","x":-1500,"y":1200,"width":1920,"height":660,"label":"Plan mega group"},
		{"id":"future-no-raws-law","type":"text","text":"## Hard boundary\n\nPhase 1 forbids:\n- transcripts\n- comments\n- full article or video ingest\n- crawler dumps\n\nreason:\nprove judgment before content volume","x":20,"y":1280,"width":320,"height":490,"color":"#8b5cf6"},
		{"id":"future-evolve","type":"text","text":"## Not discussed enough\n\nevolve loop\ndisagreement summaries\npolicy updates","x":-360,"y":1570,"width":320,"height":220,"color":"#f97316"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-audit-loop","type":"text","text":"## Evolution loop\n\nTier 1 run\n-> audit markdown\n-> Duc audit\n-> dataset rows\n-> prompt audit\n-> next tier proposal","x":1515,"y":2190,"width":270,"height":230,"color":"#8b5cf6"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-objective","type":"text","text":"## Tier 1 objective\n\noptimize for:\nwhy Duc would click\n\nTier 1 is attention triage,\nnot truth judgment.","x":600,"y":1745,"width":235,"height":190,"color":"#fdba74"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-reason-codes","type":"text","text":"## Reason-code shape\n\npositive_pull[]:\n- novel_angle\n- concrete_outcome\n- operator_energy\n- clear_pain\n\nnegative_push[]:\n- guru_fluff\n- generic_topic\n- status_bait\n- fake_specificity","x":600,"y":2020,"width":330,"height":400,"color":"#fdba74"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-prompt-contract","type":"text","text":"## Prompt contract\n\nspeak in direct taste language:\n\"would Duc click this?\"\n\nDo only:\n- explain title pull\n- explain preview pull\n- emit sexy_label\n- emit positive_pull[]\n- emit negative_push[]\n- emit final_verdict\n\nstay metadata-only","x":900,"y":1245,"width":280,"height":415,"color":"#fdba74"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-audit-artifact","type":"text","text":"## Audit markdown\n\nshow only:\n- title\n- description_or_preview\n- Raven output\n- Duc audit line\n\nHuman audit stays plain language.","x":980,"y":2273,"width":260,"height":295,"color":"#8b5cf6"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-contract","type":"text","text":"## Tier 1 contract\n\ninput:\n- title\n- description_or_preview\n- lightweight metadata\n\noutput:\n- sexy_label\n- positive_pull[]\n- negative_push[]\n- title_pull\n- preview_pull\n- final_verdict","x":1240,"y":1605,"width":275,"height":415,"color":"#fdba74"},
		{"id":"future-trust","type":"text","text":"## Intended feature\n\nchannel trust\nS / A / B / C / D\nevidence accumulation","x":-460,"y":1270,"width":320,"height":220,"color":"#8b5cf6"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-labels","type":"text","text":"## Label set\n\nskip\nmaybe\nclick\nmust_click\n\nThis tracks attraction first,\nnot epistemic quality.","x":1880,"y":1713,"width":260,"height":255,"color":"#fdba74"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-score-split","type":"text","text":"## String-rich judgment\n\ntitle_pull\n= what in the title attracts or repels\n\npreview_pull\n= how the preview reinforces or weakens the click impulse\n\nfinal_verdict\n= final natural-language click judgment","x":1890,"y":1245,"width":240,"height":395,"color":"#fdba74"},
		{"id":"future-law","type":"text","text":"## Session law\n\nPlan mega group holds session-general pressure only.\nGroup-specific draft belongs in that group's (Draft) space.\n\nEvolution must run through evidence,\nnot vibes.","x":-1100,"y":1560,"width":680,"height":270,"color":"#8b5cf6"},
		{"id":"future-judgment","type":"text","text":"## Session focus\n\nTier 1 ranker contract\n+ first taste-ingestion pipeline\n+ evolution through evaluation runs","x":-840,"y":1270,"width":320,"height":220,"color":"#f97316"},
		{"id":"ranking-draft-automation","type":"text","text":"## Automation boundary\n\nautomatic:\n- run ranker\n- render audit md\n- build dataset rows\n- audit prompt\n\nhuman gate:\n- audit labels\n- approve new tier version","x":1960,"y":2135,"width":290,"height":340,"color":"#8b5cf6"},
		{"id":"future-open-questions","type":"text","text":"## Session questions\n\n- what is the exact Tier 1 contract?\n- how should audits become dataset rows?\n- how should prompt audit feed the next version?\n- what becomes automatic vs human-approved?","x":-1410,"y":1240,"width":520,"height":280,"color":"#8b5cf6"},
		{"id":"future-memory","type":"text","text":"## Session loop\n\neval run\n-> human-readable audit md\n-> Duc audit\n-> dataset rows\n-> prompt audit\n-> next Tier 1 version","x":-1410,"y":1560,"width":260,"height":260,"color":"#0f766e"},
		{"id":"create-run-card","type":"text","text":"## create_run\n\nFirst graph node.\n\nCreates `raven_runs` row from the target query and puts `run_id` + `db` into graph state.","x":-1880,"y":-65,"width":280,"height":212,"color":"#ccfbf1"},
		{"id":"enricher-card","type":"text","text":"## enricher\n\n`Raven_graph.py`\n\nturns one rough target into a small set of search-ready query variants for the rest of Raven","x":-1240,"y":-62,"width":308,"height":206,"color":"#f97316"},
		{"id":"youtube-search-card","type":"text","text":"## youtube_search\n\ncalls YouTube search for one query and reshapes the raw API response into Raven-style query and candidate blocks","x":-578,"y":-49,"width":270,"height":180,"color":"#60a5fa"},
		{"id":"raven-law","type":"text","text":"## Current runtime truth\n\n`Raven_graph.py` now owns the live pass:\n\nSTART -> create_run -> enricher -> youtube_search -> Send(ranker_tier1) -> ranker_tier1_final -> END\n\nSearch is no longer only outside the graph skeleton.","x":-1740,"y":315,"width":600,"height":235,"color":"#8b5cf6"},
		{"id":"model-split-card","type":"text","text":"## Model/key split\n\n`LOW_LLM_KEY`\n-> enricher + Tier 1\n-> `gpt-5.4-mini`\n\n`HIGH_LLM_KEY`\n-> final selector\n-> `gpt-5.5`\n\nThis is the current uncommitted repo change.","x":-1086,"y":214,"width":216,"height":336,"color":"#f97316"},
		{"id":"tier1-send-card","type":"text","text":"## ranker_tier1_route\n\nGets all query ids for the run.\n\nLoads Tier 0 candidates per query.\n\nReturns LangGraph `Send` calls so each candidate is scored separately.","x":-618,"y":299,"width":350,"height":229,"color":"#fdba74"},
		{"id":"tier1-ranker-node","type":"text","text":"## ranker_tier1 (live node)\n\nmetadata-only attention triage\n\nreads persisted candidate dict:\n- id\n- title\n- description\n\nwrites back to `raven_candidates`:\n- `sexy_label`\n- reasoning currently stored in `final_verdict`\n\npull arrays still empty; no transcript/content judgment","x":70,"y":41,"width":390,"height":462,"color":"#fdba74"},
		{"id":"tier1-state-card","type":"text","text":"## Parallel join state\n\n`ranker_tier1_results` uses `Annotated[list[dict], add]` so parallel candidate results accumulate before final selection.","x":680,"y":187,"width":350,"height":170,"color":"#ede9fe"},
		{"id":"tier1-final-card","type":"text","text":"## ranker_tier1_final\n\nHigh-model consolidation node.\n\nReads labeled candidates for the run, builds readable `PACKET` blocks, calls Noctua, then writes one decision per candidate:\n\n`keep` or `throw_out` + reason","x":1200,"y":-78,"width":360,"height":265,"color":"#f97316"},
		{"id":"tier1-packet-card","type":"text","text":"## Final packet shape\n\nEach block contains:\n- candidate_id\n- query\n- tier1_label\n- title\n- tier1_reasoning\n\nStill metadata-only, not source evidence.","x":1200,"y":299,"width":360,"height":310,"color":"#ede9fe"},
		{"id":"legend","type":"text","text":"# Audit rule\n\nDeep marine = SQL / state\nOrange = AI\nLight blue = search\nPurple = other\n\nOriginal color = live cards and plan-only cards\nLighter same color = actual unfinished function or feature\n\nArchitecture in scope goes through Canvas first\nFunction-local code planning stays out","x":1500,"y":-1720,"width":360,"height":380,"color":"#1e293b"},
		{"id":"search-entry","type":"text","text":"## search_youtube\n\n`search_base.py`\n\nloops over `queries`\ncurrently just calls `youtube_search(query)`","x":-1440,"y":-1587,"width":245,"height":205,"color":"#60a5fa"},
		{"id":"youtube-call","type":"text","text":"## youtube_call\n\nraw API request\n`search.list`\nHTTP + JSON","x":-944,"y":-1564,"width":220,"height":160,"color":"#60a5fa"},
		{"id":"search-duration-card","type":"text","text":"## Duration fan-out\n\n`youtube_search.py` runs `search.list` twice:\n- medium\n- long\n\nThen dedupes video IDs before enrichment.","x":-987,"y":-1135,"width":305,"height":275,"color":"#60a5fa"},
		{"id":"video-enrichment-card","type":"text","text":"## videos.list enrichment\n\nBatches video IDs into chunks of 50.\n\nPulls:\n- snippet\n- statistics\n\nMerges enriched rows back by video ID.","x":-357,"y":-1127,"width":330,"height":260,"color":"#60a5fa"},
		{"id":"tier0-filter-card","type":"text","text":"## Tier 0 filter\n\nCandidate survives only when:\n\n`view_count >= 40000`\n\nOutput stays metadata-only: title, description, channel, link, publish time, views.","x":295,"y":-1115,"width":330,"height":235,"color":"#60a5fa"},
		{"id":"youtube-result","type":"text","text":"## YoutubeSearchResult\n\n`query_list`\n`candidates_list`\n`error`","x":320,"y":-1564,"width":280,"height":155,"color":"#60a5fa"},
		{"id":"packing-gap","type":"text","text":"## Search bridge\n\n`search_base.py` now packs enriched YouTube results into SQLite.\n\nLive smoke passed: query row, API log, candidate rows, candidate logs.","x":-1456,"y":-694,"width":278,"height":245,"color":"#ede9fe"},
		{"id":"db-gap","type":"text","text":"## SQLite seam\n\ncurrent: `create_query`, API logs, candidate rows, and candidate logs are connected through `search_youtube`.\n\nnext consumer: Tier 1 ranker","x":-724,"y":-666,"width":560,"height":190,"color":"#ccfbf1"},
		{"id":"candidate-row-rank-fields","type":"text","text":"## Candidate row now carries rank state\n\n`raven_candidates` stores both triage and final selection fields:\n\n- sexy_label\n- positive_pull / negative_push\n- title_pull / preview_pull\n- final_verdict\n- final_decision / final_reason","x":320,"y":-729,"width":335,"height":315,"color":"#ccfbf1"}
	],
